        {
            "heading": "FIP Calculator: What It Is and How It Works",
            "content": "The FIP Calculator evaluates a pitcher’s Fielding Independent Pitching (FIP), a metric focusing only on outcomes the pitcher controls: home runs allowed (HR), walks (BB), hit-by-pitch (HBP), strikeouts (K), and innings pitched (IP). Formula: FIP = ((13 × HR) + (3 × (BB + HBP)) − (2 × K)) ÷ IP + C. C is a league constant to scale FIP similar to league-average ERA."
